President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. Luke J. McCormack will be appointed as Chief Information Officer of the Department of Homeland Security. Edmund J. Malesky will be appointed as a member of the Board of Directors of the Vietnam Education Foundation. Elisa Spungen Bildner and John Farahi will be appointed as members of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Lastly, Dana M. Perlman will also be appointed as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. President Obama expressed his confidence in these individuals and looks forward to working with them in the future.